8 (1) The Governor shall not enter into an agreement pursuant to 8 U.S.C.
9 § 1357(g) or 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i) without prior approval from the General
10 Assembly.
11 (2) Not fewer than 60 days before the General Assembly may vote on a
12 proposed agreement pursuant to subdivision (1) of this subsection, the
13 Governor shall:
14 (A) provide the General Assembly with:
15 (i) the full text of the proposed agreement; and
16 (ii) an analysis of the potential fiscal, social, and legal impacts of
17 the agreement; and
18 (B) hold one or more public hearings in order to inform and gather
19 input from Vermonters, including immigrant advocacy organizations, on the
20 proposed agreement.

